  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/spikes/003-message-id-strategy.md` exists and documents the chosen strategy + evidence.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GraphMessageIdResolver` (or inline equivalent) exists and is registered in `CommunicationModule`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`CommunicationService.SendAsync()` calls the resolver AFTER `SendMail` succeeds; failure logs a warning but does NOT throw.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Single retry + 1-second backoff on resolver failure (not chained).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Outbound `sprk_communication` record receives `sprk_internetmessageid` value on successful resolution.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` clean; existing `dotnet test` passes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta reported in PR description; ≤ +0.5 MB expected.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new HIGH CVEs.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">End-to-end dev smoke: outbound → reply → inbound resolver matches via stamped field (evidence in task notes).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The spike has a HARD 1-hour cap. If strategy (a) and (b) both fail in 1 hour, escalate to human with the evidence — do not improvise a third strategy unilaterally.

    Strategy (a) (correlationId extended property) is preferred because it's deterministic. Strategy (b) (receivedDateTime + subject) is acceptable but produces false positives in high-volume mailboxes with duplicate subjects (e.g., "Re: meeting").

    DI registration is in `CommunicationModule` only (per ADR-010 + bff-extensions.md). If the resolver needs Graph + Dataverse, inject both via existing module abstractions; do NOT create a new abstraction layer.

    Task 008 covers unit tests for the new code path (success case + retrieval-failure case). Task 007 deploys the changes to dev. Both depend on this task.

    Per CLAUDE.md §10 bullet 6 + spec.md §5.5: tests MUST follow per `bff-extensions.md` test obligation. PR description for task 003 must state "tests in task 008."
  </notes>

